l. 29. longinquitate, best taken of time = ‘ duration.’ She had been forgotten so long that none would ask how she died.

l. 2. scripsit. The tense is merely an aorist; whereas that of ⁶ crede- bantur’ is used to express the belief at the time when the letters were written. With ‘ compositae,' ‘ suisse' is to be supplied.
